{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:joshua.15",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "joshua",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Joshua 15 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:1",
      "text": "The lot for the tribe of the people of Judah according to their families reached southward to the boundary of Edom, to the wilderness of Zin at the farthest south.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:2",
      "text": "And their south boundary ran from the end of the Salt Sea, from the bay that faces southward;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:3",
      "text": "it goes out southward of the ascent of Akrabbim, passes along to Zin, and goes up south of Kadesh-barnea, along by Hezron, up to Addar, turns about to Karka,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:4",
      "text": "passes along to Azmon, goes out by the Brook of Egypt, and comes to its end at the sea. This shall be your south boundary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:5",
      "text": "And the east boundary is the Salt Sea, to the mouth of the Jordan. And the boundary on the north side runs from the bay of the sea at the mouth of the Jordan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:6",
      "text": "and the boundary goes up to Beth-hoglah, and passes along north of Beth-arabah; and the boundary goes up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:7",
      "text": "and the boundary goes up to Debir from the Valley of Achor, and so northward, turning toward Gilgal, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, which is on the south side of the valley; and the boundary passes along to the waters of En-shemesh, and ends at En-rogel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:8",
      "text": "then the boundary goes up by the valley of the son of Hinnom at the southern shoulder of the Jebusite (that is, Jerusalem); and the boundary goes up to the top of the mountain that lies over against the valley of Hinnom, on the west, at the northern end of the valley of Rephaim;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:9",
      "text": "then the boundary extends from the top of the mountain to the spring of the Waters of Nephtoah, and from there to the cities of Mount Ephron; then the boundary bends round to Baalah (that is, Kiriath-jearim);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:10",
      "text": "and the boundary circles west of Baalah to Mount Seir, passes along to the northern shoulder of Mount Jearim (that is, Chesalon), and goes down to Beth-shemesh, and passes along by Timnah;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:11",
      "text": "the boundary goes out to the shoulder of the hill north of Ekron, then the boundary bends round to Shikkeron, and passes along to Mount Baalah, and goes out to Jabneel; then the boundary comes to an end at the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:12",
      "text": "And the west boundary was the Great Sea with its coast-line. This is the boundary round about the people of Judah according to their families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:13",
      "text": "According to the commandment of the Lord to Joshua, he gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh a portion among the people of Judah, Kiriath-arba, that is, Hebron (Arba was the father of Anak).",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:14",
      "text": "And Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak, Sheshai and Ahiman and Talmai, the descendants of Anak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:15",
      "text": "And he went up from there against the inhabitants of Debir; now the name of Debir formerly was Kiriath-sepher.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:16",
      "text": "And Caleb said, “Whoever smites Kiriath-sepher, and takes it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter as wife.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:17",
      "text": "And Othni-el the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it; and he gave him Achsah his daughter as wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:18",
      "text": "When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field; and she alighted from her ass, and Caleb said to her, “What do you wish?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:19",
      "text": "She said to him, “Give me a present; since you have set me in the land of the Negeb, give me also springs of water.” And Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:20",
      "text": "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Judah according to their families.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:21",
      "text": "The cities belonging to the tribe of the people of Judah in the extreme South, toward the boundary of Edom, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:22",
      "text": "Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:23",
      "text": "Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:24",
      "text": "Ziph, Telem, Be-aloth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:25",
      "text": "Hazor-hadattah, Keri-oth-hezron (that is, Hazor),",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:26",
      "text": "Amam, Shema, Moladah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:27",
      "text": "Hazar-gaddah, Heshmon, Beth-pelet,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:28",
      "text": "Hazar-shual, Beer-sheba, Biziothiah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:29",
      "text": "Baalah, Iim, Ezem,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:30",
      "text": "Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:31",
      "text": "Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:32",
      "text": "Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: in all, twenty-nine cities, with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:33",
      "text": "And in the lowland, Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:34",
      "text": "Zanoah, En-gannim, Tappuah, Enam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:35",
      "text": "Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:36",
      "text": "Sha-araim, Adithaim, Gederah, Gederothaim: fourteen cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:37",
      "text": "Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal-gad,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:38",
      "text": "Dilean, Mizpeh, Joktheel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:39",
      "text": "Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:40",
      "text": "Cabbon, Lahmam, Chitlish,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:41",
      "text": "Gederoth, Beth-dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteen cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:42",
      "text": "Libnah, Ether, Ashan,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:43",
      "text": "Iphtah, Ashnah, Nezib,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:44",
      "text": "Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:45",
      "text": "Ekron, with its towns and its villages;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:46",
      "text": "from Ekron to the sea, all that were by the side of Ashdod, with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:47",
      "text": "Ashdod, its towns and its villages; Gaza, its towns and its villages; to the Brook of Egypt, and the Great Sea with its coast-line.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:48",
      "text": "And in the hill country, Shamir, Jattir, Socoh,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:49",
      "text": "Dannah, Kiriath-sannah (that is, Debir),",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:50",
      "text": "Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:51",
      "text": "Goshen, Holon, and Giloh: eleven cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:52",
      "text": "Arab, Dumah, Eshan,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:53",
      "text": "Janim, Beth-tappuah, Aphekah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.54",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:54",
      "text": "Humtah, Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron), and Zior: nine cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.55",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:55",
      "text": "Maon, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.56",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:56",
      "text": "Jezreel, Jokde-am, Zanoah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.57",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:57",
      "text": "Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.58",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:58",
      "text": "Halhul, Beth-zur, Gedor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.59",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:59",
      "text": "Maarath, Beth-anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.60",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:60",
      "text": "Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), and Rabbah: two cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.61",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:61",
      "text": "In the wilderness, Beth-arabah, Middin, Secacah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.62",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:62",
      "text": "Nibshan, the City of Salt, and En-gedi: six cities with their villages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:joshua.15.63",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "joshua",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Joshua 15:63",
      "text": "But the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the people of Judah could not drive out; so the Jebusites dwell with the people of Judah at Jerusalem to this day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
